This paper deals with the problem of constructing a data aggregation tree in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI) as well as data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also considers the cases where relay nodes exist and the link quality is not perfect, which are topics related to system and control theory (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
